The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and database management, which are both subfields of computer science. Specifically, it focuses on Text-to-SQL, which falls under the category of NLP. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with databases and schema linking, which are related to cs.DB (Databases) sub-category. The use of neural networks and machine learning techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, which are related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
